# Accessibility Standards

## Voice Input Accessibility

1. Provide clear visual indicators for voice input status
2. Include proper ARIA labels for voice controls
3. Implement keyboard alternatives for voice features
4. Show clear feedback for voice recognition status
5. Handle errors with clear user feedback

## General Accessibility

1. Use semantic HTML elements
2. Implement proper heading hierarchy
3. Ensure sufficient color contrast
4. Provide alt text for images
5. Support keyboard navigation

## ARIA Implementation

1. Use appropriate ARIA roles
2. Implement proper ARIA states
3. Add descriptive ARIA labels
4. Use ARIA live regions for dynamic content
5. Follow WCAG guidelines

## Focus Management

1. Implement logical focus order
2. Provide visible focus indicators
3. Handle focus trapping in modals
4. Manage focus after dynamic updates
5. Support skip links

## Input Methods

1. Support multiple input methods
2. Implement proper touch targets
3. Handle different input devices
4. Provide alternative text input methods
5. Support screen readers properly
